main event: A small pen-shaped object was observed while traveling at a 33-degree elevation on a heading of 156 degrees.
interesting points: The object was described as having a pea shape and was observed using binoculars., The observation lasted for approximately 1 minute and 15 seconds., The visibility conditions were 20 miles with scattered cumulus clouds., It was evaluated as a potential satellite by naval officers., Multiple witnesses including lookout personnel were involved in the observation.
